        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If you're trying to provide a custom count query, don't forget to add the zend_paginator_row_count column in the columns part of the query. There's a constant for this in the DbSelect adapter class.\nAlso, the adapter adds the limit and offset parts automatically, so there's no need to do that yourself.\nI'm closing this as Not an Issue. Please provide some more details if you do think this is a bug :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-23T13:36:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-23T13:36:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23020",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satanistlav",
                        "name": "satanistlav",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Anisimov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that the offset part is not needed in counting rows. Selecting rows count with offset part will always return null if offset is greater  than 0\nEx: select count(*) from bugs LIMIT 10  OFFSET 30\n\nHere are my actual examples:\n\nThis code throws the exception\n{code}\n           $bugsTable        = new Bugs();\n            $bugsRowset    = $bugsTable->find(1234);\n            $bug1234          = $bugsRowset->current();\n            \n            $productsTable = new Products();\n            $productsRowset   = $bug1234->findManyToManyRowset('Products', 'BugsProducts', null, null, $select = $productsTable->select()->limitPage(2, 10));\n            \n            $paginator = Zend_Paginator::factory($select)->\n                                    setCurrentPageNumber(2)\n                                        ->setItemCountPerPage(10);\n{code}\n\n\nThe code works fine after I clear the offset limit part of the select\n{code}\n            $bugsTable        = new Bugs();\n            $bugsRowset       = $bugsTable->find(1234);\n            $bug1234          = $bugsRowset->current();\n            \n            $productsTable = new Products();\n            $productsRowset   = $bug1234->findManyToManyRowset('Products', 'BugsProducts', null, null, $select = $productsTable->select()->limitPage(2, 10));\n            \n            $paginator = Zend_Paginator::factory($select->reset(Zend_Db_Select::LIMIT_OFFSET))->\n                                    setCurrentPageNumber(2)\n                                        ->setItemCountPerPage(10);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satanistlav",
                        "name": "satanistlav",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Anisimov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-23T14:15:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-23T14:15:56.000+0000"
                },
